-- FACTBOX: Key facts about U.S. December auto sales
-- 
-- Thu Jan 3, 2008 7:35pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/04/us-autos-sales-idUSN0324946020080104

 

 (Reuters) - U.S. December auto sales fell 2.9 percent from a year earlier, according to data from auto manufacturers on Thursday. The following are highlights from the largest carmakers in the U.S. market. 

 Overall industry * Total light vehicle sales -- 1.39 million units. General Motors Corp ( GM.N ) * Light vehicle sales down 4.4 percent (319,837 units) * Year-to-date sales down 6.3 percent * Inventories at month-end: just over 900,000 units * Cars/trucks: Cars down 10 percent/light trucks down 2.3 percent * Retail sales: Retail up 1.5 pct * Market share: 23 percent * Key vehicles: Chevrolet Impala down 32 percent, Chevrolet Malibu up 6.7 percent, Chevrolet Silverado up 2.2 percent, Chevrolet Tahoe down 25.6 percent, GMC Sierra up 12.8 percent. * Incentives: average $3,563 per vehicle, up from $2,228 a year earlier. Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T )( TM.N ) * Vehicle sales down 1.7 percent (224,399 units) * Year-to-date sales up 2.7 percent * Market share: 16.2 percent * Cars/trucks: Cars down 1.7 percent/trucks down 1.8 percent * Key vehicles: Tundra up 54.1 percent, Camry down 1.8 percent, Prius up 53 percent, Corolla down 2.7 percent * Incentives: averaged $1,063 per vehicle, up from $972 a year earlier. Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) * Vehicle sales down 9.2 percent (212,094 units) * Year-to-date sales down 12 percent * Inventories at month-end were 533,000 units, down from 570,000 units year earlier * Retail/fleet mix: Retail sales of Ford, Lincoln, Mercury down 13 percent/fleet sales down 1 percent * Cars/trucks: Cars down 8.4 percent/trucks down 9.5 percent * Market share: 15.2 percent * Key vehicles: F-Series down 22 percent, Explorer down 18.7 percent, Expedition down 30.2 percent, Fusion up 7 percent. * Incentives: averaged $2,996 per vehicle, down from $3,795 a year earlier. Chrysler LLC * Car and light truck sales up 0.52 percent year over year (191,423 units) * Year-to-date sales down 3 percent * Cars/trucks: Cars down 3 percent/trucks down 2 percent * Market share: 13.8 percent * Inventories at month-end were 438,390 units, or a 60-day supply, down 19 percent from year ago. * Key vehicles: Jeep Wrangler up 4 percent, Dodge Ram pickup down 2 percent, Dodge Caliber down 6 percent. * Incentives: average $3,340 per vehicle, down from $4,178 a year earlier. Honda Motor Co ( 7267.T )( HMC.N ) * Car and light truck sales flat year over year (131,792 units) * Year-to-date sales up 2.5 percent * Market share: 9.5 percent * Cars/trucks: Cars up 10.2 percent/trucks down 10.3 percent * Key vehicles: Accord up 4.6 percent, Civic up 15.2 percent, CR-V up 7.6 percent. * Incentives: averaged $960 per vehicle, up from $577 a year earlier. Nissan Motor Co Ltd ( 7201.T ) * Car and light truck sales down 2.4 percent year over year (89,555 units) * Year-to-date sales up 4.5 percent * Market share: 6.4 percent * Cars/trucks: Cars down 0.3 percent/trucks down 5.3 percent * Key vehicles: Versa up 49.8 percent, Altima up 1.3 percent, Sentra down 5.9 percent, Titan down 14.2 percent. * Incentives: average $2,080 per vehicle, up from year $1,704 a year earlier. (Reporting by  Poornima Gupta )